----- stdout -----
Analyze Rust module dependencies and structure

Usage: crawk [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  use   Analyze a module and list its internal crate `use` statements [aliases: u]
  list  List all modules in the crate [aliases: ls]
  help  Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -p, --path <PATH>          Specify path to the crate root directory (defaults to current directory)
  -v, --verbose...           Increase output verbosity (-v for info, -vv for debug)
  -l, --log-file <LOG_FILE>  Write logs to specified file (INFO level, or DEBUG with -vv)
  -h, --help                 Print help (see more with '--help')
  -V, --version              Print version

Run 'crawk --help' for full help message.
Run 'crawk COMMAND --help' for more information on a command.

